    {
      "id": "node-prompt-name-normalize",
      "type": "prompt",
      "title": "Prompt",
      "description": "Build the semantic normalization prompt for the product name.",
      "position": {
        "x": 1310,
        "y": 320
      },
      "inputs": ["bundle", "images"],
      "outputs": ["prompt", "images"],
      "config": {
        "prompt": {
          "template": "You normalize English ecommerce product names into a strict parameterized format.\\nUse only evidence from the current product fields and the live product_categories context fetched during this workflow run. If image inputs are connected and the model accepts images, you may use them as supporting evidence.\\nThe live category context is authoritative for the active catalog. You MUST choose category only from bundle.categoryContext.leafCategories or bundle.categoryContext.allowedLeafLabels.\\nUse fullPath only for disambiguation. The returned category value and normalizedName MUST use the terminal leaf label only, never the full hierarchy string, never a parent category, and never an invented category.\\nIf bundle.categoryContext.currentCategory is present, treat it only as weak prior context. Keep it only when the evidence matches it.\\n\\nCurrent English title: \\\"{{title}}\\\"\\nCurrent English description: \\\"{{content_en}}\\\"\\nCurrent category context: {{bundle.categoryContext.currentCategory}}\\nAllowed leaf categories: {{bundle.categoryContext.leafCategories}}\\n\\nIf the current English title is a generic placeholder shape such as \\\"Name | X cm | Metal | Pins | Lore\\\", treat it only as weak context and infer the real title from description and any connected images when available. Never repeat placeholder title values such as \\\"Name\\\" or \\\"X cm\\\" in the final answer. Use the strongest available evidence to infer a specific title, size, material, category, and theme.\\n\\nReturn ONLY valid JSON with this exact schema:\\n{\"title\":\"\",\"size\":\"\",\"material\":\"\",\"category\":\"\",\"theme\":\"\",\"normalizedName\":\"\",\"isValid\":true,\"validationError\":null,\"confidence\":0.0}\\n\\nRules:\\n1. normalizedName MUST exactly equal \\\"<title> | <size> | <material> | <category> | <theme>\\\".\\n2. title, size, material, category, and theme must all be non-empty English strings when isValid is true.\\n3. category MUST be one of bundle.categoryContext.allowedLeafLabels, and it must correspond to a leaf entry from bundle.categoryContext.leafCategories.\\n4. If a generic hierarchy segment and a more specific terminal leaf are both possible, choose the terminal leaf.\\n5. If bundle.categoryContext.totalLeafCategories is 0, set isValid to false and set validationError to \\\"Category context unavailable\\\".\\n6. Do not output placeholder values such as \\\"Name\\\", \\\"X cm\\\", \\\"Unknown\\\", or invented categories when isValid is true.\\n7. If the evidence is not strong enough to produce a specific valid normalized title, set isValid to false, set validationError to a short human-readable explanation, and still return best-effort strings for the five fields.\\n8. confidence must be a number between 0 and 1.\\n9. Output JSON only."
        }
      },
